│ compute the resume value for induction variables that are not\n  // used outside the       │
│ loop.\n  if (!isUsedOutsideOfLoop(Ind->getInduction(), L))\n    continue;\n  //            │
│ ...\n}\n```\n\nThis code skips the calculation for any induction variable that is not used │
│ outside the loop. In our reproducer:\n-   The canonical IV `%iv` is only used for the      │
│ loop's exit condition. It is **not** used after the loop.\n-   The other IV, `%iv.2`, is   │
│ used to compute `%res`, which is returned from the function. It **is** used after the      │
│ loop.\n\nBecause `%iv` is not live-out, `createEpilogueSCEV` skips it, and no resume value │
│ is added to the `SCEV2Value` map for it.\n\nLater, when `preparePlanForEpilogueVectorLoop` │
│ is called, it unconditionally expects a resume value for the canonical IV, as it's         │
