│ finds nothing, triggering the assertion.\n\nThe fix is to recognize that the canonical     │
│ IV's resume value is *always* needed for the epilogue, regardless of whether it's used     │
│ outside the loop. We must remove the `isUsedOutsideOfLoop` check for the canonical         │
│ IV.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\n\nThe fix is to modify                               │
│ `LoopVectorizePass::createEpilogueSCEV` to ensure it always computes the resume value for  │
│ the canonical induction variable.\n\n**File**:                                             │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp`\n\n```cpp\n// Edit at line 9758\nfor     │
│ (auto *Ind : Inductions) {\n  // No need to compute the resume value for induction         │
